The paper discusses the security aspects of 5G networks, which falls under the category of network security. Therefore, cs.NI (Network and Distributed Systems Security) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the evolution of computing paradigms for enhancing security, which can be related to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also proposes a security model, which can be related to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SE (Software Engineering).
